NUMBER 3635
NAME By a Black Altar
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This hidden and serene clearing in the woods is dominated completely by a huge black altar, carved into the shape of a wolf sitting on its haunches. It regards you coldly and impassively. Next to it, an opening leads deeper into the woods.
*DESCRIPTION_END
FOREST
DAY_LIGHT
ITEM 0 72  VAL2=3636
ITEM 1 236  ADJ1=25  ADJ2=312
EXTEND 1 shaped like a huge wolf
EXIT O 126
IFPREVERB GO 0
  IFVAR ITEMVAL5 ! 1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER The altar's eyes flash briefly red as a strange force pushes you back!
    ECHO OTHERS %N tries to go through %a, but then the altar's eyes flash briefly red and %s is thrown back!
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB RECALL -1
  IFVAR RAC = 4
    ECHO PLAYER You recall strange tales you heard as a cub of a black stone altar guarding the tomb of an ancient warrior. To pass, you must say its name and then pass three tests.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY BLACKPELT
  IFVAR CHASPUZZLE ! 0
    ECHO ALL A voice speaks: "I have already been identified today"
  ENDIF
  IFVAR CHASPUZZLE = 0
    EQUAL CHASPUZZLE 1
    ECHO ALL A voice speaks: "You have named me. If you wish to enter my resting place, you must hear my tale and defeat my three challenges, the challenge of heart, the challenge of mind, and the challenge of claw. If you accept these conditions, say 'I accept' and prepare for the first challenge."
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB2 PUT 1
  IFVAR CHASPUZZLE = 4
    IFVAR ARCHNUM = 521
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER The altar accepts your offering.
      ECHO OTHERS %N places %a on the altar, whose eyes flash briefly.
      REMOVEITEM -1
      EQUAL CHASPUZZLE 5
      PLREVENT 1
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL A voice speaks: "And so Blackpelt gathered his wolves and led them on a final assault against the enemy, gathering them in a narrow valley. The weres swarmed upon them, outnumbering them ten to one, and the wolves began to break ranks, trembling with fear. But then Blackpelt gave forth a mighty howl, and the birds and squirrels and deer and bears and all the creatures of the forest appeared, fighting the werewolves alongside the members of the tribe."
      PLREVENT 3
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL A voice speaks: "But still it was not enough, for the chief of the accursed fought with the strength of ten. But then Blackpelt himself joined the fray. Whether it was the strength of Shemri, or his natural strength, he turned the tide. Finally he and the great were faced off as the battle carried on around them."
      PLREVENT 3
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL A voice speaks: "They clawed and bit, holding back nothing. It was a fight of attrition, for each was as skilled as the other. Blackpelt was a little faster, but the accursed chieftan was a little stronger. Finally, Blackpelt managed to weave under his opponent's defenses, tearing out his enemies throat, only to have his back broken by a single crushing blow."
      PLREVENT 3
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL A voice speaks: "With the death of their chieftan, the werewolves howled in anguish and tried to flee, but were quickly cut down by the surviving wolflings. And so the battle was won, though Blackpelt lay wounded on the field. By sundown, he was dead."
      PLREVENT 2
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL A voice speaks: "That night, the howls of the wolflings filled the air... triumphant howls of victory, and sad howls of mourning for the dead. And so it was that the accursed were driven from the woods, never again reaching the strength they had attained. And so did the battlefield, this valley, become a sacred shrine to the wolflings, for a crypt was built and Blackpelt's body was placed within, at the very spot where he died."
      PLREVENT 3
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL A voice speaks: "By passing the three challenges you have shown yourself worthy of the memory of this great leader of old. The way now lies open to you"
      ECHO ALL The eyes of the altar flash, and a shimmering haze vanishes from around the opening into the valley.
      SETITEMVAL 0 5 1
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFVAR CHASPUZZLE = 3
    IFVAR ARCHNUM = 509
      IFVAR ITEMADJ2 = 559
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER The altar accepts your offering
        ECHO OTHERS %N places %a upon the altar, and its eyes flash briefly.
        REMOVEITEM -1
        EQUAL CHASPUZZLE 4
        PLREVENT 1
        CONTPLREVENT
        ECHO ALL A voice speaks: "It was then, when all seemed lost, that he arrived. A wolf as black as the night who never once spoke a word. Some thought he was an avatar of the Wolf Mother herself, others fancied him a warrior from a tribe far to the south. But he had come, and his name was Blackpelt."
        PLREVENT 3
        CONTPLREVENT
        ECHO ALL A voice speaks: "He gathered the tattered remnants of the tribe and led them into battle against the accursed. Under his leadership victories were won, and the weres were pushed back a little. But it looked as though it was too late, for the enemy seemed as numerous as the trees themselves."
        PLREVENT 3
        CONTPLREVENT
        ECHO ALL A voice speaks: "The final challenge is one of mind. Bring me the one thing Blackpelt lacked if you with to pass."
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFVAR CHASPUZZLE = 2
    IFVAR RAC = 4
      IFVAR ARCHNUM = 509
        IFVAR ITEMADJ2 = 568
          IFVAR ALIGN >= 0
            CLEARVERB
            ECHO PLAYER The altar accepts your offering.
            ECHO OTHERS %N places %a on a black altar, and its eyes flash briefly.
            REMOVEITEM -1
            EQUAL CHASPUZZLE 3
            PLREVENT 1
            CONTPLREVENT
            ECHO ALL A voice speaks: "That night a council was convened to discuss the problem of the re-emergence of the ancient foe. But times had been good for too long, and they did not appreciate the real threat. The next day the four best hunters of the tribe were sent to slay the accursed ones. They never returned."
            PLREVENT 3
            CONTPLREVENT
            ECHO ALL A voice speaks: "In the weeks that followed, many more of the tribe fell victim to the accursed's foul claws. It was clear that soon they would be no more."
            PLREVENT 3
            CONTPLREVENT
            ECHO ALL A voice speaks: "The second challenge is one of claw. When you are ready, say 'My claws are sharp'.
          ENDIF
        ENDIF
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY MY_CLAWS_ARE_SHARP
  IFVAR CHASPUZZLE = 3
    ECHO ALL Several bits of shadow detach themselves and move towards you.
    GENMON 98
    GENMON 98
    GENMON 98
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFSAY I_ACCEPT
  IFVAR CHASPUZZLE = 1
    ECHO ALL A voice speaks: "Excellent. Here is the first part of the story of Blackpelt."
    PLREVENT 1
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO ALL A voice speaks: "Ages ago, when the world was a different place, there was a time when none of our sacred enemies, the werewolves, lived in this forest. Game was plentiful, and our race flourished, growing fat and complacent. Times were peaceful for so long that many of us forgot the ways of war, and our claws grew dull. Some saw danger in this, but for the most part their warnings went unheeded."
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO ALL A voice speaks: "And so things were for several generations, until even the loudest of voices had fallen all but silent. It was then that trouble struck. The hunters returned home one day to find Realla, one of the smallest cubs, lying in a pool of blood, her neck broken, surrounded by an ancient scent they knew only from stories."
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO ALL A voice speaks: "Your first challenge is a challenge of heart. You must prove your wolfling blood by placing a pelt of our accursed enemy upon my idol."
    EQUAL CHASPUZZLE 2
  ENDIF
ENDIF
NUMBER 3636
NAME A Valley of Bones
CALL 33
 
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This is a narrow valley, hidden within the depths of the forest. A great feeling of death and sadness lies over it, and you can almost hear voices in the howling winds. Bones litter the valley floor; bones of wolflings and of werewolves and of every species of forest creature imaginable. A dark crypt lies in the center of the valley, with a simple arch leading in.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ASTRAL
DAY_LIGHT
EXIT O 3635
ITEM 0 60  VAL2=3637
ITEM 1 233
IFTOUCH 1
  IFVAR RAC = 4
    ECHO PLAYER You feel a faint shiver, deep within, as you touch the bones.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR RAC ! 4
    ECHO PLAYER You hear a faint scream far away, and you realize you have violated something sacred.
    GMMSG %N just got cursed by the ghosts of dead wolflings. Please treat %i accordingly.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
