NUMBER 3639
NAME House of the Elder Wolf
CALL 33
 
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This simple chamber is sparsely decorated, with a small woven mat and two incense burners to either side. On it, cross-legged, an aging wolfling rests, still fit despite his years. A small sign has been posted by the gate, and a set of strap-on claws hang from a hook nearby.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
ITEM 0 68  VAL2=3524
ITEM 1 1122
ITEM 2 204
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 2
Mastery of claws taught here --
any supplicants seeking to learn mastery (or specialization, as it is sometimes called) of the claws must remove the albescent claws from the hook and wield them.
*DESCRIPTION_END
PUT 1 651  ADJ1=1130
UNLOCK 0
IFPREVERB GO 0
  CLEARVERB
  IFCARRY 651 -1
    ECHO PLAYER The aged wolfling stops you, saying, "You cannot leave this place with the albescent claws."
  ELSE
    ECHO OTHERS %N goes out through a gate.
    MOVE 3524
    AFFECT 3524
    ECHO OTHERS %N arrives.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFENTRY
  ECHO ALL An aged wolfling bows to %N, saying, "Enter, supplicant, and learn the true mastery of the claw."
ENDIF
IFPREVERB DEPART -1
  IFCARRY 651 -1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You cannot depart from here with the albescent claws.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB SELFTRAIN -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You cannot do that here.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB TEACH -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You will have to do that somewhere else.
ENDIF
